history.content: Summer capacity is not infinite so we can't promise every will get in -- especially to upper division classes where our limiting factor is often availability of qualified TAs to staff additional discussion sections.  If we can find additional TAs, then new sections will be opened and the waitlist will be notified to have first shot at enrolling in the new sections.

I am currently waitlisted for the summer class in CS 160 (31/60). What are the chances of me getting into the class? Is CS160 one of those classes where everyone is able to get in?  I am an EECS major
history.subject: Summer - CS 160 Waitlist
